The paper deals with differential privacy, hypothesis testing, and sample complexity, which are all topics that fall under the umbrella of computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves statistical learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS) in the context of designing efficient algorithms for hypothesis testing. Finally, the paper may be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI) since differential privacy is often used to protect sensitive information in these domains.
